cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AR, cs.AI. 

The paper focuses on optimizing the hardware implementation of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) using binary and ternary weights, which is a topic related to neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method on various sequential models, including language modeling and sequence classification, which are related to natural language processing and computer vision, respectively. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) are also likely categories. Finally, the paper proposes custom hardware for accelerating the recurrent computations of LSTMs, which is related to artificial intelligence and hardware design, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category as well.
